"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"d'Oyré","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Duinn</b>, <b>Ó Doinn</b> (see   Dunne  ); this is an earlier Anglicization.","English: variant of   Dean   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Dunne","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Dermot, Kieran, Liam, Cahal, Eamonn, Grainne.","Chinese: variant of   Dunn  .","German (<b>Dünne</b>): nickname for a slender, skinny person, from Middle High German <i>dünne</i> ‘thin’."]},{"name":"Doyen","meanings":["Altered form of Irish   Doyne  .","French: from <i>doyen</i> ‘dean’, hence probably a nickname for someone thought to resemble a dean, or an occupational name for someone in the service of a dean."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert d'Oyré was born in 1211, in Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1270, in Drayton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1211–1270":"1211–1270","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1211–1270":"1211–1270","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1211–1270":"1211–1270","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert d'Oyré est né en 1211, à Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1270, à Drayton, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 59 ans."},"de":{"1211–1270":"1211–1270","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1303":"1303","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1299":"1299","1270":"1270","Oyré, Châtellerault, Vienne, Aquitaine":"Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Frankreich","Drayton, Hellesden, Norfolk, England":"Drayton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert d'Oyré wurde 1211 in Oyré, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Frankreich geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn und 1 Tochter. Er starb 1270 im Alter von 59 Jahren in Drayton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1211–1270":"1211–1270",